---
/**
 * transactions-isolation-fundamentals · Figure 5 — Level 7, the 2PC IN-DOUBT
 * trap (participant voted YES, coordinator then crashes → block).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/transactions-isolation/transactions-isolation-fundamentals.html (figure +
 * svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the MDX,
 * because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attrs.
 *
 * The source page defines the arrowhead markers once in a top-of-body
 * <svg defs> (#arw grey, #arwA red, #arwG green). This figure references #arwA,
 * so it is inlined here in a local <defs> (verbatim from that defs block) so the
 * marker-end="url(#…)" references resolve standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A participant that voted yes and lost its coordinator can neither commit nor abort, so it blocks holding locks"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="280"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">THE IN-DOUBT TRAP</text
            >
            <rect x="200" y="32" width="160" height="34" rx="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="48"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">participant voted YES</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="61" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >coordinator then crashes</text
            >
            <rect x="20" y="100" width="160" height="38" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="100" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110"
                >can't COMMIT</text
            >
            <text x="100" y="129" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >maybe verdict was ABORT</text
            >
            <rect x="380" y="100" width="160" height="38" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text x="460" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110"
                >can't ABORT</text
            >
            <text x="460" y="129" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >maybe verdict was COMMIT</text
            >
            <path d="M 240 66 L 130 98" fill="none" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwA)"></path>
            <path d="M 320 66 L 430 98" fill="none" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwA)"></path>
            <rect x="210" y="100" width="140" height="38" rx="8" fill="#1c1b18"></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="116"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#f3efe3">BLOCK</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="129" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#e8b3a6"
                >hold locks, wait for recovery</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        This is the Two Generals Problem with a tie-breaker: one node decides, the rest obey — but
        if that node dies mid-decision, the rest freeze.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
